[2026-01-22 00:46:54] [INFO] Full LLM response:
The problem asks to prove the injectivity of the map $j_1: D \to D \otimes_{\mathbb{Z}} \hat{\mathbb{Z}}$, where $D$ is the rational Hurwitz quaternion algebra and $\hat{\mathbb{Z}}$ is the profinite integers. The map $j_1$ is the base change of the natural inclusion $\mathbb{Z} \to \hat{\mathbb{Z}}$ along the $\mathbb{Z}$-module $D$.

The injectivity follows from two facts:
1.  The map $\mathbb{Z} \to \hat{\mathbb{Z}}$ is injective (since $\hat{\mathbb{Z}}$ has characteristic 0).
2.  The module $D$ is flat over $\mathbb{Z}$. This is because $D = \mathbb{Q} \otimes_{\mathbb{Z}} \mathcal{O}$, and both $\mathbb{Q}$ and $\mathcal{O}$ (being a free $\mathbb{Z}$-module) are flat over $\mathbb{Z}$, and the tensor product of flat modules is flat.

